% 
% ==============================================================
% === KEY ======================================================
% ==============================================================
% 
% The 'world' (.k1) filename can be up to 8 characters as of svn revision 10017.
% (This is backwards compatable and 6 can still be used.)
% 
% The translation of the character positions is as follows:
% 
% 1-2 ==  input code:
%         fk == 'fake'
% 3   ==  resulting:
%         h == 'high' == 36x36
%         l == 'low'  == 18x18
% 4   == n/a
% 5-6 ==  continental configuration code:
%         pp == 'pole-to-pole'
% 7   == n/a
% 8   ==  number of shelf steps:
%         0 == (none)
%         l == level 15
%         2 == level 15 + 14
%         3 == level 15 + 14 + 13
%         4 == level 15 + 14 + 13 + 12
%         5 == level 15 + 14 + 13 + 12 + 11
%                            
% ==============================================================
% === CONFIGURATION LIST =======================================
% ==============================================================
% 
% NOTE: where shelves are present, they are positioned on all ocean-facing sides of land
%       the addition of shelves removes land area, keeping ocena volumn approximately invarient
%       i.e. you could look at the appearance of, or increase in, the number of shevles, as a progressive flooding of the craton
%       the shallowest possible (level 16) shelf is omitted as it is impossible to represent a biological pump in the ocean
%       all configurations assume modern S0 and pO2, orbits, ocean Ca/Mg, and (preindustrial) pCO2 and 13C
% 
% --------------------------------------------------------------
% --------------------------------------------------------------
% world   | created ...       | muffingen | *BRIEF* NOTES
% name    | by, on (dd/mm/yy) | version   | (enclosed in "")
